South Africa has reached an unprecedented level of power blackouts. Read all our Eskom coverage here. Eskom cut 7 045 megawatts from the grid — a practice known as load shedding — spokesman Sikonathi Mantshantsha said in a Tweet on Tuesday. He confirmed that Eskom had moved to the so-called Stage 7. The last announcement from the utility was that it was implementing Stage 6, where it removes 6 000 megawatts. Evening Peak Feedback 21/02/2023, 19:15
Total demand: 30 480MW
Load shedding: 7 045MW
Eskom OCGT’s Utilised: 14
Eskom GT’s Utilised: 3
IPP OCGT’s: 5
Renewable Gen: 1 262MW (Wind 791MW, CSP 390MW, PV 81MW)@Eskom_SA Available Generation: 23 289MW@EskomSpokesper1 — SikonathiMantshantsh (@SikonathiM) February 21, 2023 South Africa has declared a state of disaster due to its energy crisis. Eskom has been forced to implement power cuts every day this year as its fleet of old and defective coal-powered stations frequently breaks down. © 2023 Bloomberg